.TH SIM 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sim \- simulate infinite yes response
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sim
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sim
continuously prints "y" to standard output in an infinite loop.
This is a minimal JLC equivalent of
.BR yes (1).
.SH EXIT STATUS
The program runs indefinitely and does not exit normally.
To stop execution, use
.B CTRL-C
or send a termination signal.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Pipe to a command that requires confirmation:
.EX
sim | some_interactive_command
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR yes (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.

